rComments: Definitely she is the BEST professor I've ever met in U of T! Absolutely LOVE her! The class is fascinating and intellectual simulating. She always encourages and helps her students. Caring for and loving her students makes her a great prof. She is a ray of sunlight in both of my academic career and life.

TBH I ended up dropping this course bc I didn't have 25 hrs a week to devote to Chinese. But I  stuck it out as long as I could bc of how sweet and encouraging she was. In general, UT's Chin. teaching approach is frustrating and misguided, but I appreciate that Liu's course challenged H Wu's unfortunate command over dept's txtbk and teaching style
She is a nice proessor if you get to know her better~
she only cares for her favorite students, but you can learn a lot in her class. Lots HW and tough tests...

This prof is so hard that she seems to be finding trouble for students. I regret taking this course. With comparison, this 3rd yr language course is harder than the 4th yr conducted by another prof. and she assigns students enough hwk to drive ppl crazy.
She is definitely a nice prof.  Yes, it's not an easy course, but I feel like I benefit a lot.
